WEBVTT

00:09:58.372 --> 00:10:01.141
There hasn't even been a global conversation yet

00:10:01.141 --> 00:10:02.561
about whether it's okay

00:10:02.561 --> 00:10:05.796
to misuse companies in this way.

00:10:05.796 --> 00:10:09.674
And what does it all mean for us?

00:10:09.674 --> 00:10:12.227
Well, an example that really haunts me

00:10:12.227 --> 00:10:14.605
is one I came across recently.

00:10:14.605 --> 00:10:16.554
And it's that of a horrific fire

00:10:16.554 --> 00:10:18.339
in a nightclub in Buenos Aires

00:10:18.339 --> 00:10:21.290
about a decade ago.

00:10:21.290 --> 00:10:23.560
It was the night before New Year's Eve.

00:10:23.560 --> 00:10:25.728
Three thousand very happy revelers,

00:10:25.728 --> 00:10:26.765
many of them teenagers,

00:10:26.765 --> 00:10:29.960
were crammed into a space meant for 1,000.

00:10:29.960 --> 00:10:31.133
And then tragedy struck,